### HIGH-10: Token Blacklist Full-Token Storage — Storage Explosion

| Field | Detail |
|-------|--------|
| **Severity** | 🟠 High |
| **Component** | [TokenBlacklist.ts](file:///d:/ai-learning-dashboard/server/src/models/TokenBlacklist.ts) + [auth.controller.ts](file:///d:/ai-learning-dashboard/server/src/controllers/auth.controller.ts#L286-L294) |
| **Impact** | Full JWT tokens (~1KB each) stored in DB; storage waste; slow blacklist lookups |

**The Problem:** Each blacklisted token stores the **entire JWT string** (~800-1200 bytes). With many logouts, the [TokenBlacklist](file:///d:/ai-learning-dashboard/server/src/types/index.ts#93-100) collection grows rapidly. The [protect](file:///d:/ai-learning-dashboard/server/src/middleware/auth.middleware.ts#122-187) middleware queries this collection on **every authenticated request** (line 145-148), doing a string-match against a potentially large table.

**Remediation:** Store only the JWT ID (`jti` claim) instead of the full token. Add `jti` to token payloads and index it.

