### LOW-06: `password` Field Select Inconsistency

| Field | Detail |
|-------|--------|
| **Severity** | 🔵 Low |
| **Component** | [User.ts](file:///d:/ai-learning-dashboard/server/src/models/User.ts#L18) |

The User model has `select: false` on password but the schema defines `minlength: 6` while [validatePassword](file:///d:/ai-learning-dashboard/app/signup/page.tsx#22-31) middleware requires `minlength: 8`. This inconsistency means the Mongoose schema allows weaker passwords than the API validation:

```typescript
// User.ts - Schema allows 6 chars
password: { type: String, required: true, minlength: 6 }

// validation.middleware.ts - API requires 8 chars
body('password').isLength({ min: 8 })
```

